<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>About Us - VigilCam</title>

  <!-- Favicon -->
  <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/public/images/favicon.png">
  <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/public/images/favicon.png">

  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/icon?family=Material+Icons" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
  <!-- Background Image -->
  <div class="background-image"></div>
  
  <%- include('partials/navbar') %>
  
  <main class="main-content">
    <%- include('partials/messages') %>
    
    <section class="about-section">
      <div class="about-header">
        <h1 class="about-title">About VigilCam</h1>
        <p class="about-subtitle">Professional AI-Powered Exam Proctoring & Surveillance System</p>
      </div>

      <!-- ML Detection Features -->
      <h2 class="feature-section-title" style="text-align: center; font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
        <span class="material-icons" style="vertical-align: middle; font-size: 2.5rem;">memory</span>
        Advanced ML Detection Capabilities
      </h2>
      
      <div class="features-grid">
        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="feature-icon">
            <span class="material-icons" style="font-size: 3rem; color: #00ffff;">face</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="feature-title">Face Detection & Tracking</h3>
          <p class="feature-description">
            Real-time multi-face detection using MediaPipe Face Detection with confidence scoring. 
            Automatically alerts when multiple faces appear or when the candidate leaves the frame.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="feature-icon">
            <span class="material-icons" style="font-size: 3rem; color: #00ffff;">visibility</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="feature-title">Gaze Tracking</h3>
          <p class="feature-description">
            Advanced iris position tracking with calibration system. Monitors where the candidate 
            is looking with precision - detects looking away, up, down, left, or right.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="feature-icon">
            <span class="material-icons" style="font-size: 3rem; color: #00ffff;">remove_red_eye</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="feature-title">Blink Detection</h3>
          <p class="feature-description">
            Eye Aspect Ratio (EAR) calculation for accurate blink detection. Tracks normal and 
            excessive blinking patterns, and detects extended eye closure (>4 seconds).
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="feature-icon">
            <span class="material-icons" style="font-size: 3rem; color: #00ffff;">record_voice_over</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="feature-title">Audio Monitoring</h3>
          <p class="feature-description">
            Real-time audio analysis using sounddevice library. Detects talking through mouth 
            movement analysis and unusual noise levels with baseline calibration.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="feature-icon">
            <span class="material-icons" style="font-size: 3rem; color: #00ffff;">3d_rotation</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="feature-title">Head Pose Estimation</h3>
          <p class="feature-description">
            Nose tip landmark tracking for head orientation analysis. Identifies when candidates 
            turn their head significantly away from the camera.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="feature-icon">
            <span class="material-icons" style="font-size: 3rem; color: #00ffff;">analytics</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="feature-title">Behavioral Analysis</h3>
          <p class="feature-description">
            Comprehensive violation detection and scoring system. Real-time risk assessment with 
            severity levels (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW) and detailed violation logging.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="feature-icon">
            <span class="material-icons" style="font-size: 3rem; color: #00ffff;">videocam</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="feature-title">Live Video Streaming</h3>
          <p class="feature-description">
            Base64-encoded JPEG streaming at 30 FPS with quality optimization. Low-latency 
            WebSocket-based communication between Python ML backend and Node.js server.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="feature-icon">
            <span class="material-icons" style="font-size: 3rem; color: #00ffff;">assessment</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="feature-title">Comprehensive Reporting</h3>
          <p class="feature-description">
            Automatic JSON report generation with session duration, violation history, risk scores, 
            and complete behavioral statistics. Downloadable for record-keeping.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="feature-icon">
            <span class="material-icons" style="font-size: 3rem; color: #00ffff;">tune</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="feature-title">Calibration System</h3>
          <p class="feature-description">
            3-second baseline calibration for gaze tracking accuracy. Establishes normal eye 
            position and audio baseline for precise anomaly detection throughout the session.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Technology Stack -->
      <h2 class="feature-section-title" style="text-align: center; font-size: 2rem; margin: 4rem 0 2rem;">
        <span class="material-icons" style="vertical-align: middle; font-size: 2.5rem;">code</span>
        Technology Stack
      </h2>
      
      <div class="features-grid">
        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="feature-icon">
            <span class="material-icons" style="font-size: 3rem; color: #00ff00;">psychology</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="feature-title">Computer Vision</h3>
          <p class="feature-description">
            OpenCV 4.x for video processing • MediaPipe Face Mesh for 468 facial landmarks • 
            MediaPipe Face Detection for multi-face tracking
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="feature-icon">
            <span class="material-icons" style="font-size: 3rem; color: #00ff00;">computer</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="feature-title">Backend</h3>
          <p class="feature-description">
            Node.js + Express.js • Python 3.8+ • Socket.IO for real-time communication • 
            PythonShell for process management
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="feature-icon">
            <span class="material-icons" style="font-size: 3rem; color: #00ff00;">storage</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="feature-title">Database & Auth</h3>
          <p class="feature-description">
            MongoDB with Mongoose ORM • Passport.js authentication • bcrypt password hashing • 
            Express sessions
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Connect With Us -->
      <div class="social-section">
        <h2 class="social-title">
          <span class="material-icons" style="vertical-align: middle; font-size: 2.5rem;">connect_without_contact</span>
          Connect With Us
        </h2>
        
        <div class="social-grid">
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/azhaanalisiddiqui/" target="_blank" class="social-card linkedin">
            <div class="social-icon">
              <span class="material-icons" style="font-size: 3.5rem; color: #0077b5;">work</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="social-name">LinkedIn</h3>
            <p class="social-handle">Professional Network</p>
          </a>

          <a href="https://github.com/AzhaanGlitch" target="_blank" class="social-card github">
            <div class="social-icon">
              <span class="material-icons" style="font-size: 3.5rem;">code</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="social-name">GitHub</h3>
            <p class="social-handle">Open Source Projects</p>
          </a>

          <a href="mailto:azhaanalisiddiqui15@gmail.com" class="social-card email">
            <div class="social-icon">
              <span class="material-icons" style="font-size: 3.5rem; color: #ea4335;">email</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="social-name">Email</h3>
            <p class="social-handle">Direct Contact</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Project Info -->
      <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 4rem; padding: 2rem; background: var(--bg-card); border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">
        <h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          <span class="material-icons" style="vertical-align: middle;">info</span>
          About This Project
        </h3>
        <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; line-height: 1.8;">
          VigilCam is a professional-grade exam proctoring system developed by <strong>Azhaan Ali Siddiqui</strong>. 
          It combines advanced computer vision, machine learning, and real-time web technologies to provide 
          comprehensive monitoring capabilities. The system is designed for educational institutions, 
          certification providers, and organizations requiring secure remote examination environments.
        </p>
        <div style="margin-top: 2rem;">
          <a href="https://github.com/AzhaanGlitch/VigilCam" target="_blank" class="btn-primary" style="display: inline-flex;">
            <span class="material-icons">star</span>
            Star on GitHub
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  
  <%- include('partials/footer') %>
  
  <script src="/js/main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>